column457: great time/reward ratio! Unpaid screeners suck though and can generate bad reviews on sites like Turk Opticon or Turkerview and can prevent people from doing your HITs in the future or possibly even trying to predict what you're looking for and alter their responses to get in to the study and make money. Maybe consider a small .05 paid screener (less than 1 minute demographics) in the future to encourage honesty.

column457: I don't recall ever checking any fact-checking sites, so I would have liked the option to pick N/A for that question. Also, the reason I chose not to share the headlines is largely twofold: 1. Enough Trump, already! There are enough other places for people to get their round-the-clock Trump bombardment. 2. I rarely use social media, and the only reason I'm starting to is for professional reasons. So probably the only reason I would currently share a political story is if it were directly relevant to my profession (if a new copyright law were passed, for example, since I'm a photographer/artist). However, that could change because I'm planning to start an online magazine that will get political, no doubt.
